	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=13270&amp;mid=108301682572873">Great Item... here's why</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=13270&amp;mid=108301682572873#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Mon, Apr 26th 6:00 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=124165"><span id=" ">mrfritz</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">7 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>From the posts i've read, people seem to be missing the best use for this item (aside from the stats of course, which are pretty nice, even well into EPs).&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickie effects don't look at the lapse time between spell casts, and Gather Shadows is Self Only, so if you have an Enchanter, Mage, or Necro who is using a charm pet, they can keep their pet targeted, click this item to break pet and follow immediately with a debuff or mez or recharm.  If you've ever used a high level charmed pet you know that it's better to have a controlled break than an uncontrolled break.  When I need to break my pet to redo debuffs i have to sit, mem imp invis, wait for it to come up, cast it, wait for spell gems to refresh, then i can finally repet... as opposed to with this clickie, where one could simply click and mez for debuffs or just repet immediately.  Having this around saves you either 1 spell slot if you keep invis up at all times, or a sufficient amount of time, when time is frequently very valuable.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
